Below is a basic example of how to set up an n8n workflow JSON snippet for integration with Bright Data's verified node. This assumes you have already configured your Bright Data credentials and n8n instance.


{
  "name": "Bright Data AI Agent Workflow",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "functionCode": "return [{ json: { query: 'latest AI news' } }];"
      },
      "id": "generate-query",
      "name": "Generate Query",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.function",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [250, 300]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "credentials": {
          "brightDataApi": {
            "id": "bright-data-cred-id",
            "name": "Bright Data API"
          }
        },
        "operation": "get",
        "path": "datasets/{{$json.query}}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "bright-data-node",
      "name": "Bright Data",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.brightData",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [450, 300]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "functionCode": "return [{
          json: {
            result: items[0].json.data,
            metadata: items[0].json.metadata
          }
        }];"
      },
      "id": "process-data",
      "name": "Process Data",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.function",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [650, 300]
    }
  ],
  "connections": {
    "Generate Query": {
      "main": [[{ "node": "Bright Data", "type": "main", "index": 0 }]]
    },
    "Bright Data": {
      "main": [[{ "node": "Process Data", "type": "main", "index": 0 }]]
    }
  },
  "active": false,
  "settings": {},
  "versionId": "1.0"
}


This workflow generates a query, fetches data using Bright Data's API via the verified node, and processes the returned data.
